metadata.name: Supernal Memories #237
metadata.description:
With its layered bursts of color, light, and shadow, Supernal Memories carries an underlying message of optimism through its harmony of seeming dualities – hard and soft, familiar and surprising, expression and introspection.

Each newly generated circle brings its own energy, creating layered groups of light that sometimes resemble phenomena like nebula, lightning sprites, and auras – ethereal whispers of something remembered. 

Supernal Memories is an invitation to observe the forms & feel of each piece without labeling their qualities, to contemplate the infinite possibilities of the universe, and to explore the depths of your imagination.


--

Created by Diego Pintos @DondiegoTez
Creative collaboration with Tender @tender_art

To get a high resolution file, add "&print=14000" to the end of the live URL / hash, using any resolution number that fits your needs. Press 's' to save the file when it is done loading.

Press 'p' to continue the animation for another variation.

100% code, made with p5.js
See license.md

metadata.name: Gkrint #199
metadata.description:
Gkrint is a celebration of minimalism, colour, and space using the humble grid, a foundation of generative art, and movement. Through this collaboration, Ballzerino and George explore the relationships between these elements.

Inspired by the timeless principles of Bauhaus design, Ballzerino carefully curated custom colour palettes and selected geometric shapes, while George encoded the creative process into an algorithm, bringing the compositions to life, and putting the CPU to work finding new and unexpected compositions within our framework.

Gkrint is Ballzerino's genesis generative art drop.

Controls:
SPACE - pause / resume
click (or tap) - change colour selection (within same palette)
hold 'f' - speed up animation

Tested on Windows / Mac / iOS / Android. Chrome recommended for the best experience.

metadata.name: Rue Parisienne #44
metadata.description:

After putting fake web3 street names in Paris, Batist & Popeye now invite you to collect them in the form of NFTs:
- Avenue Vitalik Buterin
- Passage Hic Et Nunc

Every hash generates a unique visual collage out of an infinity possible combinations.

metadata.name: Décollage #53
metadata.description:
A generative sketch based on the concept of décollage, an artistic process that involves cutting or tearing pieces of an original image. The resulting outputs bear a resemblance to artworks produced using the lacerated poster technique, where posters are layered and torn to reveal parts of the posters underneath.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels. Note that this will not work with sizes beyond 5000 pixels.

(Allowlist is based on quantity of previous works owned).

metadata.name: VOODOOZ #59
metadata.description:
Need some luck, happiness, and lucky charm? Alexis Bacci’s VOODOOZ are here for you! Will you dare to mint and to collect?

VOODOOZ is a collection of 512 magical dolls of 3 types: basic, collector and boss - with or without accessories; a tribute to Voodoo culture entirely hand drawn by the comics author Alexis Bacci.

Each VOODOOZ doll has specific and unique magical powers, bringing luck and happiness, a lucky charm in your journey in the NFTs world!

Voodooz come with optional accessories: the SNAKE, the POTION and the RING.

• The SNAKE can complete the inner circle of life and vital energy
• The POTION will help the doll to spell, protect and increase its skills
• The RING gives more power and can be used as a talisman
• The HOLY TRINITY gathers the 3 accessories above

Tip: try to grab a SNAKE + a POTION + a RING and a special VOODOOZ NFT will be airdropped to your wallet for free.

Alexis Bacci is a comics book author who has been working in the cartoon and movie industry for two decades. In 2021 he minted his 1st NFTs on ETH, the Tengu Diaries, and his Girlz series on Tezos.

VOODOOZ are Alexis’ genesis series on fx(hash), pay attention!

metadata.name: Harmony #2
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

'Harmony' is somewhat inspired by the beautiful stain glass window designs of Frank Lloyd Wright (1867-1959).

Each 'Harmony' output is an attempt to find beauty (harmony) within the chaos created by a swirl of colors, shapes, lines and curves.

To download a 1500x2000px PNG:
Click/tap 'open', then click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear.

metadata.name: dreams #56
metadata.description:
As in a dream, this representation flows, changes direction and evolves.
Each piece represents one different dream. Calm down, nightmares, crossroads, triumphs, longings, forgotten memories, hopes, disappointments... Some have two faces, one light and one dark where sleep flows. Others have a central theme from where our dream is born or dies, in hope or in despair. Others, just flow.

--

metadata.name: Expression #17
metadata.description:
Face can be a canvas, painted with emotion and thought. Each expression tells a story, a tale waiting to be sought. From wrinkles to lines and creases, the face is a storybook, revealing secrets and emotions that we try to overlook. A smile can light up a room, bringing joy to those nearby, while a frown can darken any space and cause one to ask why. The eyes are said to be the windows to the soul that lies within, revealing the truth and deepest secrets that we try to keep hidden. Whether it's love, anger, fear or sadness, our face will always express, the feelings we hold within us and the thoughts we repress. So take a moment and read the faces that you see, for they may hold a story that's waiting to be set free.
_

Open / live mode / fullscreen view :
* press [s] on keyboard to save or download in PNG format

_

Generative visual, hybrid techniques, textures source created with AI (Stable Diffusion), combine with other elements that made with code / javascript, and layers transform in autonomous system on WebGL.
